formatted_items.content:
Here’s what I found:

1) Most-recent email from Lisa Green  
Subject: “Inquiry about Social Work in the Community”  
Date: Mon, 21 Feb 2022  
From: lisa.green@urbantimes.com  

Body:  
Dear John Doe,

I hope this message finds you well. I am writing a feature for the Urban Times on the impact of social work in urban communities, and I would love to include your insights and experiences in our piece. Could you share your thoughts on:  
• key challenges you face as a social worker,  
• any successful programs you’ve been a part of, and  
• how you see the role of social work evolving in the community?  

Thank you for considering my request. I look forward to your response.

Best regards,  
Lisa Green

2) Relevant Notion pages / notes

• “Reflections on Social Work”  
  – High-level reflection on the profession’s rewards & challenges.  
  – Mentions two standout programs you’ve helped lead:  
    ◦ Bright Futures After-School Program (safe after-school environment, improved academics & social skills)  
    ◦ Second Chance Adult Education Initiative (adult diploma/GED pathway, better job prospects)

• “Community Program Successes”  
  – Expands on Bright Futures and Second Chance outcomes.  
  – Highlights measurable community impact (safer spaces for youth, higher adult employment/education rates).  

Let me know if you’d like a bullet-point draft or talking points pulled from these notes for your reply.
